  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. The decimal equivalent of 6% is 0.06. Since increasing the number <span class=\"italic\">n</span> by 6% yields the number 318, this situation can be represented by the equation <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"n  times, open parenthesis, 1 plus 0 point 0 6, close parenthesis, equals 318\"></span>, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"n times 1 point 0 6, equals 318\"></span>. Dividing both sides of this equation by 1.06 yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"n equals 300\"></span>.<p>Choice A is incorrect. This is the result when <span class=\"italic\">n</span> is increased by 60%, not by 6%. Choice B is incorrect. This is the approximate result of decreasing 318 by 6%. Choice D is incorrect. This is the approximate result of increasing 318 by 6%.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
